# Mobile App ‚Äì Expo Patterns

## Data layer: Legend-State ‚Üí Supabase (no SQLite, no Drizzle, no TanStack Query for app data)

All synced data lives in Legend-State observables (`lib/store/index.ts`), persisted to MMKV and synced to Supabase via `syncedSupabase`. Never call the Supabase REST API directly for CRUD ‚Äî mutate the observables.

```typescript
// Read (reactive) ‚Äî components use the observable hooks
import { wallets$ } from '@/lib/store';
import { use$ } from '@legendapp/state/react';
const wallets = use$(wallets$);

// Write ‚Äî via helpers in lib/supabase/*.ts which set() into the store;
// Legend-State syncs to Postgres in the background
wallets$[id].set({ ...wallet, name: 'Updated' });

// Delete ‚Äî soft delete only (synced tables have a `deleted` column)
```

New synced table checklist: migration adds `created_at`/`updated_at`/`deleted` + RLS + realtime ‚Üí add observable in `lib/store/index.ts` ‚Üí CRUD helper in `lib/supabase/`.

## MMKV instances (lib/mmkv/)

- `auth` ‚Äî Supabase session storage (client uses `EXPO_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_PUBLISHABLE_KEY`)
- `legend-store` ‚Äî observable persistence
- `image-uploads` ‚Äî receipt upload queue
- `preferences` ‚Äî local UI prefs (theme: light / dark / system; default wallet id cache for AI fallback)

## AI pipeline (lib/ai/)

Input ‚Üí `processing-queue.ts` (MMKV) ‚Üí `background-processor.ts` (Android FG service) ‚Üí `run-extraction.ts` ‚Üí `lib/ai/client` (HTTP ‚Üí Go backend when `EXPO_PUBLIC_AI_API_URL` set, mock otherwise) ‚Üí `proposed_transactions` ‚Üí review modal. Chat tab also routes finance Q&A via `lib/ai/chat/` ‚Üí `/v1/chat/analyze`.

- Client results are `{ status: 'ok' | 'skipped' | 'unavailable' }` ‚Äî never throw across this boundary
- Wire types in `lib/ai/client/types.ts` must match `apps/backend/internal/extract/types.go`
- Notification prefilter is on-device (`lib/notifications/notification-filter.core.js`). Headless-shared helpers: see rule `mobile-headless-js` (`*.core.js` + thin `*.ts`). Wallet‚Äìapp linking: `notification_package` on wallets + MMKV linked-package cache; installed app labels/icons via `modules/moni-android-apps` (Android 11+ `<queries>` in module manifest + `plugins/with-notification-listener-manifest.js`; rebuild dev client after native/manifest changes).

## Routing (expo-router)

`app/(auth)` unauthenticated; `app/(tabs)` main tabs (Wallets / Summary / Chat / Profile); `app/(routes)` stack screens. Auth guard in `app/_layout.tsx`.

## Styling (Uniwind)

Tailwind via Uniwind `className` ‚Äî **not** NativeWind. Design tokens live in `global.css`:

- Brand scale: `--color-brand-*` in `@theme`
- Semantic light/dark: `--color-background`, `--color-primary`, etc. in `@layer theme` `@variant`
- Screens use semantic utilities (`bg-primary`, `text-foreground`, `bg-canvas`) ‚Äî never hardcode brand hex
- JS color props (charts, tab bar, icons): `useThemeTokens()` from `@/hooks/use-theme-tokens`
- Theme preference: `lib/theme/preference.ts` ‚Üí `Uniwind.setTheme('light' | 'dark' | 'system')`; default **light**
- Shared chrome: `components/ui/brand-header`, `screen-shell`, `chip`, `primary-button`

## Receipt camera (Android)

`components/receipt/receipt-camera.tsx` (FAB scan + chat inline camera) uses `modules/moni-document-scanner` (Nitro) ‚Üí Google ML Kit native document scanner. Post-scan: `lib/receipts/normalize-scan.ts` (copy + 1024px cap). **Android only** ‚Äî other platforms show an unsupported message. Requires Google Play Services; rebuild dev client after native module changes (`npx expo run:android`).
